'''Sickness''' is a negative status [[property]] that occurs in ''[[NetHack]]''. If left untreated, sickness will result in a [[delayed instadeath]] after some amount of turns. The main causes are eating too old corpses, special attacks, and cursed unicorn horns. The main remedies are applying a non-cursed [[unicorn horn]], casting {{spell of|cure sickness}}, and quaffing certain [[potions]].

The game uses "deathly sick" to specifically herald this condition, whereas there are many [[#Other uses of "sick"|other cases]] where you simply "feel sick".

[[Sickness resistance]] in vanilla NetHack is possessed only by [[ghoul]]s, which happily feast on old [[corpse]]s, and [[fungus|fungi]].{{refsrc|polyself.c|77|version=NetHack 3.6.0}}

Contrary to its name, [[potion of sickness]] does not cause sickness.

==Types of sickness==

There are two distinct types of sickness, indicated separately on the [[status line]]. You can also suffer both conditions simultaneously. The effects and remedies are identical, except that only food poisoning can be cured by [[vomiting]].{{refsrc|you.h|268|comment=lists the two independent types of SICK: SICK_VOMITABLE an SICK_NONVOMITABLE.}}

===Food poisoning===

'''Food poisoning''' is only acquired by [[eat]]ing an old ("tainted") [[corpse]] or [[glob]]. It is marked by the text <code>FoodPois</code> on the status line. The initial time until death is set to 10&ndash;19 turns.{{refsrc|eat.c|1270}}

Food poisoning is completely preventable in vanilla [[NetHack]] if you don't eat old corpses. A corpse is too old to eat after 6&nbsp;&times; (9&nbsp;+&nbsp;1d20) turns, where 6 is replaced with 8 if blessed and 4 if cursed.{{refsrc|eat.c|1253}} Corpses left by [[undead]] except [[wraith]] are always pre-aged by 100 turns; eaten immediately, they have 40% chance of causing food poisoning. Old corpses can be rendered safe to eat by [[tinning kit|tinning]] them. [[Lichen]] and [[lizard]] corpses never rot and may be safely eaten regardless of age.

Despite the name, food poisoning is unrelated to [[poison]] and is unaffected by [[poison resistance]].

{{upcoming|NetHack 3.7.0|You have a constitution in 100 chance of surviving food poisoning. If you do, you lose 1 point of constitution and abuse constitution.}}

===Illness===

'''Illness''' is conferred by the '''disease''' attacks of certain monsters, listed below, or by applying a [[cursed]] [[unicorn horn]]. It is marked by the text <code>Ill</code> on the status line.
*{{monsym|Demogorgon}} [[Demogorgon]]
*{{monsym|Juiblex}} [[Juiblex]]
*{{monsym|Scorpius}} [[Scorpius]]
*{{monsym|Pestilence}} [[Pestilence]]

The first time you contract the illness, a turns-to-live timer is started, set to between 20 and (19+[[Con]]). Each additional illness attack while you are <code>Ill</code> divides the remaining turns-to-live by roughly 3.<ref>{{sourcecode|mhitu.c|773}}, {{sourcecode|apply.c|1458}}</ref>

==Remedies==
Sickness can be easily cured with any of the following:
*[[apply]]ing a non-cursed [[unicorn horn]]{{refsrc|apply.c|1541}}
*[[pray]]ing to your god
*quaffing a non-cursed potion of {{of|potion|extra healing|or=1|full healing}}, a blessed [[potion of healing]], or (unless chaotic) a [[potion of holy water]]
*casting a [[spellbook of cure sickness|spell of cure sickness]]
*eating a non-cursed [[eucalyptus leaf]]{{refsrc|eat.c|1725}}
*invoking [[the Staff of Aesculapius]]{{refsrc|artifact.c|1219}}

The full list of less common remedies also includes:
* vomiting from eating [[Tripe ration|tripe]] or a rotten [[egg|egg]]. This cures food poisoning only, not illness. Quite unreliable, but it's there.
*[[polymorph]]ing into a new version of yourself{{refsrc|polyself.c|190}} or a [[Sickness resistance|sickness-resistant]] monster{{refsrc|polyself.c|1411}} ([[ghoul]] or some [[fungi]]). (A new version includes if you "fail" to change form, but get your attributes adjusted.)
*getting healed by a [[nurse]]'s attack.{{refsrc|mhitu.c|1407}}
*sitting on a [[throne]] ({{frac|13}} chance).{{refsrc|sit.c|188}}

The only sure-fire cures are the potions, prayer if safe, the spell at 0% failure rate, and polyself. A [[unicorn horn]] is good enough if you weren't made sick multiple times.

Importantly, ''[[poison resistance]] is not a remedy''; if you become food poisoned and rely on this you will die.

